Section 2 of the Bill states: This Bill applies to:(a) an assault causing serious harm to an emergency worker whilst he or she is on duty;
(b) a threat to kill or cause serious harm to an emergency worker whilst he or she is on duty; or
(c) an injury to an emergency worker whilst he or she is on duty caused by the piercing of that emergency worker with a syringe.We need to be very careful about the victims of assaults and trying to prevent assaults under the law. There can never be a hierarchy of victims where some victims get more sympathy and more coverage in the media than others. We need to be very cautious and ensure that everyone is treated with respect and equality.
